  <DocumentNotes>
    <Note Title="Summary" Type="General" Ordinal="1">A vulnerability in the TFTP server feature of Cisco IOS and Cisco IOS XE Software could allow an unauthenticated, remote attacker to cause a denial of service (DoS) condition.



The TFTP server feature is not enabled by default.



Cisco has released software updates that address this vulnerability. 



Workarounds that mitigate this vulnerability are available.



This advisory is available at the following link:

http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityAdvisory/cisco-sa-20150722-tftp["http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityAdvisory/cisco-sa-20150722-tftp"]</Note>
